 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">La statue du</supplied> roi Ptolémée, grand Dieu, Evergète, fils des Dieux Epiphanes,
            <supplied reason="subaudible">a été consacrée</supplied>, par les gardes du corps aspirants <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">avec le long</supplied> épieu,
            les <foreign rend="italic">hypaspistes</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation">écuyers</supplied>, les soldats d'élite et bien d'autres en raison de sa bienveillance et de sa générosité envers eux.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">The statue of</supplied> king Ptolemy, great God, Euergetes, son of the Gods Epiphaneis,
            <supplied reason="subaudible">was dedicated</supplied> by the body-guards cadets <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">with the long</supplied> spear,
            the <foreign rend="italic">hypaspistes</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation">esquires</supplied>, the choosen soldiers and many others on behalf of his goodwill and generosity towards them.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">La statua del</supplied> re Tolemeo, Grande Dio Evergete, figlio degli Dèi Epifani,
            <supplied reason="subaudible">è stata dedicata</supplied> dai cadetti delle guardie del corpo <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">con la lunga</supplied> lancia,
            dagli <foreign rend="italic">hypaspistes</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation">scudieri</supplied>, dai soldati scelti e da molti altri per la benevolenza e generosità nei loro confronti.</p>
         </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
                <p>(تمثال) الملك بتوليميوس (بطليموس)، المُؤله المُعظم، إفيريغيتس، ابن المؤلَّهان إبيفانيس، (كُرِس) من قبل نائب الحُراس الشخصيين [مع الطويل؟] الرمح، وحملة الدروع (المحترمين)، والجنود المختارين وآخرون كُثر لخيره وكرمه عليهم.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For the whereabouts of the stone, see commentary at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr097500</ref>.</p>
	       <p>This dedication of a statue of king Ptolemy VIII Euergetes II by diginitaries has been commented and restored without exact consideration
	       of the dimensions of the gap at the beginning of the lines. The missing part may be estimated from the opposite side. Pugliese Carratelli at 
	       <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/></bibl> was right in restoring 4 to 6 letters, whereas Piejko's restorations (<bibl><ptr target="#piejko1981"/></bibl>) are too long.</p>
	       <p>Especially at line 3, Piejko's proposal was sceptically received by the Roberts at <bibl><ptr target="#robertBE"/>1982.491</bibl> who did not understand the supposed meaning; 
	           furthermore, Piejko's argument that <foreign xml:lang="grc">συβίνη</foreign> is a feminine is not fully convincing, as a masculine <foreign xml:lang="grc">συβίνης</foreign> did also exist.</p>
                 <p>At line 4, <foreign xml:lang="grc">εὐνοίας</foreign> does not deserve Piejko's scepticism, see for example <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr063000</ref>.</p>
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#lanciers1988"/></bibl> has shown that Ptolemy bore the title Euergetes already when king of Cyrene, i.e. from 164 on.</p>
            </div></body>
